  "prompt": "How should aloe vera plants be watered?",
  "response": "Here are some key tips for watering aloe vera plants:\n\n1. Watering frequency\n- Water sparingly\n- Allow soil to dry completely between waterings\n- Typically water every 2-3 weeks\n- Reduce watering in winter when plant is dormant\n\n2. Soil moisture\n- Aloe plants prefer well-draining soil\n- Overwatering can cause root rot\n- Use a pot with drainage holes\n- Use cactus or succulent potting mix\n\n3. Watering technique\n- Water deeply but infrequently\n- Water at the base of the plant\n- Avoid getting water on the leaves\n- Let excess water drain completely\n\n4. Seasonal considerations\n- Water more frequently during growing season (spring/summer)\n- Reduce water in fall and winter\n- Adjust based on humidity and temperature\n\n5. Signs of improper watering\n- Yellowing or soft leaves = overwatering\n- Wrinkled or brown leaves = underwatering\n\n6. Environmental factors\n- Less water needed in humid environments\n- More water needed in hot, dry climates\n- Indoor plants typically need less water than outdoor plants\n\nAlways check soil moisture before watering and adjust based on your specific plant's needs.",
